It's me, Lucas. The new adventurer. Sorry you had to pick up my buddy Claus's slack, but thanks for taking care of that delivery for us. I have another favor to ask you. Could you help a guy out? Claus started going on about taking on a monster bounty, but we don't stand a chance at our skill level. Could you talk some sense into him?!

I'm an adventurer and scholar by the name of Lestor. I got caught up in a storm while carrying an important package to Asterliese and couldn't do anything to retrieve them. You seem like an adventurer who can hold their own, and this package must be delivered! For the future of all humanity! Please, lend me your aid!

Hi, hello! My name is Tynie. I work as a maid at a lovely manor with a lovely runaway cat. That's injured. It's...not great. So I'm looking for the little furball the best I can, but the best I can is...also not great. Think you can help me out? If you pitched in with the search, that'd be...kind of great, actually? Thanks.

Hey yo. I'm Cyril, a Templar for the Bapharian Church. I had a teensy little favor I needed to ask an adventurer. See, there's this SPECIAL INGREDIENT I just can't get my hands on. Can't tell you more than that! If you wanna know more, come see me at the Bapharian outpost in the <value type="locationName" id="[SQ101_032_area1]"/>. I'm countin' on ya!

Hey, it's Mirleen. I gave instructions that this quest was to be posted if Walken doesn't come home after five days. So basically, if you're reading this? You know what happened. Ugh. He's probably fixated on some excavation stuff on the Asteria Plains, so could you give him a hand? He's probably running low on food too. Knowing him, he's gonna throw a fit about how he won't go home until he's done with his excavation, so... good luck with that.

Oh, just LOOK at your clothes! Okay, I just HAVE to ask you. I've been desperately looking for adventurers/fashion gurus, okay? Okay, so, my name is Thierry, and I'm a brand-spakin' new fashion designer! So like, I'm trying to get this new brand off the ground, right? Probably is, I just don't have enough manpower, y'know? I need someone who can get me materials for the sake of the fashion world at large! Could you maybe pretty please with a cherry on top get me some? Thankiiiie!

The name is Luke, an aspiring warrior. I've seen what you are capable of and wish to ask you for your assistance. I would like to craft a token with which I can express my resolve. I am aware this should be a job I take myself, I fear I will not have time without help. Please, I ask your assistance! I beg of you!

The name is Feodore, a scholar, aspiring to create a perfectly accurate weather reporting system. I'm hoping to record some observations around the Asteria Plains, and I imagine I'll need someone who can handle themselves around monsters to do the deed. It won't take long to collect the data I need. Won't you please help me?

Hullo, adventurer! I'm an apprentice chef here in Asterliese by the name of Bert. The head chef gave me some homework to do and it's... let's just say, I'm not doing too hot on my own. I'm begging you, adventurer! Help me make this a meal worth celebrating!

Hi, I'm Radym! I'm on a pilgrimage to sacred Bapharian sites with my mom and dad! Problem is, on the way we ran into some <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ101_116_enemy1]"/> and haven't been able to get anywhere. I don't DISLIKE the travel and stuff, but it's been days and I'm BORED! So could you come out and get rid of the <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ101_116_enemy1]"/> for us?!

Hi there! I'm Syree, apprentice restorer of Bapharian artifacts extraordinaire! You know about crafting, right? Of course you do! And you know the Spheromutator? Well that's just one big ol' ball of Bapharian tech! It's so huge and imposing and sturdy and... Sorry about that. Anyway, the inner workings of it are super fine and complex, so they need to get checked on from time to time. And I kinda don't have what I need for it. Could you help a girl out?

I'm Remigio, and I'm gonna be the best merchant there ever was! It's my motto that there's nothing wrong with some give and take! So... could I get you to maybe 'give' me your help apologizing for something big? Like, there's someone I REALLY, REALLY need to apologize to, but I'm too chicken to do it myself... Please help me, adventurer! I need you to come with me! I swear I'll do it, but I need someone to do it with me!

'Sup? The name's Darla. I'm a fellow adventurer. So I'm out looking for some sand viper deltoid scales per the Development Bureau's request, right? Well, some damn land hawks came outta nowhere and snatched up my weapon. I might be tough, but I ain't tough enough to finish this request barehanded. So could you pick up those sand viper deltoid scales for me?

FOR THE LOVE OF ALL THAT IS HOLY, HELP ME! Okay, lemme slow down. My name is Carlione, and I'm a newly appointed Templar. My captain told me I needed to go kill some monsters.
...BUT THERE'S NO WAY! I CAN'T DO IT! WHY DOES EVERYONE THINK I CAN?! The captain said none of us are going home 'til we defeat enough of them either! You're my only hope, adventurer! Please, please, please! HELP ME!

Name's Panayote. Just a lowly Bapharian priest. I've got a buncha crap to take care of, but I figured I could clean up some trash on the road while I'm at it. I'm plannin' on sweepin' the road between Salamzahd and Hermit's Spring today. Problem is, there's a lotta monsters partyin' out that way lately. I'm gonna need me an adventurer with a good arm on 'em. If you're up for bein' a guard and a janitor, hit me up.

Welcome, welcome! I got your lunchboxes right here! Okay, maybe I don't at the MOMENT. I messed up when I was ordering my ingredients and got it from Montegnor by accident. I NEED them to be Erstgreen or the flavor'll be all messed up! Could you help me fix this mess?

Nyeh-heh-heh... Hello there. It's me, Leik. The potionmaster. You starting to get used to my laugh? Excellent. Love to hear that. Nyeh-heh-heh. Now, remember that transformation potion? I still need a few more... unusual ingredients for it. This time it's monster parts, and getting them might prove to be a bit... hairy. I can't ask the Bureau or any other adventurers or they'll find out about my potion. You're the only one I can count on. We've already come so far together... Don't let me down now, adventurer... Nyeh-heh-heh...

Hey there. It's Brandel the blacksmith. I've been trying out some of those ancient crafting techniques, but the weapons just aren't holding up like I want 'em to. Did a bit of researchin' and it says you gotta have ore AND monster parts for it. Thing is, I'm not quite sure how to get a hold of 'em. You're the only adventurer I know. Couldja gimme a hand?

I'm Lasha, wife of the head honcho of the mining operations in Rietz. I look after the miners and manage our finances and records. Lately, we've had a bunch of <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_036_enemy1]"/> hanging out around our mines. We can't just leave them be, so every once in a while we like to have a culling. Think you can handle a little bit of <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_036_enemy1]"/> culling?

Oh, Adventurer, do I have an offer for YOU! The name's Galvin, and I'm a merchant lookin' into local delicacies and other such specialties. And lemme tell ya, Rietz definitely has some of those. You ever heard of a thing called a golden barbel? They're supposed to bring good luck. And wouldn't you know it? I saw a big ol' school of 'em in a river recently. If we catch that much, we'll be SWIMMIN' in cash! So whaddya say? Ready to make some major moolah?

My name is Trathe, and I'm soon departing on a journey. Y'see, I've gotten my hands on an echo that can capture scenery, and I'm hoping to do just that. I want to travel the world, gathering as many views as I can for... someone very important to me. I'd like to start by taking some time in the areas around Rietz. But traveling can get pretty dangerous, so I'd like someone who could keep me safe. You think you can do that?

HAH HAH HAH! IT IS I, THE GREAT DETECTIVE GUIDO! Wherever there is a mystery, I will shine the light of truth upon it! But alas! This case I've been chasing is quite the head-scratcher, even for my massive and powerful brain! I call it... the Case of the Camel Caper! The culprit has never been seen, and the camels they steal seem to vanish into thin air... What say you, junior detective? Care for a bit of mystery?!

My name is Ardlung, and I'm a jeweler. I was traveling with some of my jewels when my cart was attacked by <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_043_enemy1]"/>s and all of my goods were stolen. I'm practically done for if I can't get it back! Please help me return my stolen inventory!

Name's Jin. Hunter from Salamzahd. Guess it was about time I asked for help. My son's undergoin' a ritual to make him a true-blue hunter. Problem is, a load of <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_044_enemy1]"/>s have shown up. I can't go in and help my son and all, but innocent people might wind up gettin' hurt if we don't thin out their numbers. Could you go in and mop 'em up real quick?

My name's Remigio, and I'm gonna be the best merchant there ever was, and I say there's nothin' wrong with a little give and take! Anyway, one of my classmates was bragging about this emblem of courage thing. I've seen all sorts of treasures from my dad before, but never anything like this! I've GOTTA have one for myself! I just know I have to get an adventurer to help me find one, though. Could you be that adventurer? I promise I'll make it worth your while!

Sup? You're an adventurer, right? Well, I'm a mercenary. Name's Suzette. I got this weird lantern thing as payment for a job I did a bit ago, but I can't make heads or tails of the damn thing. I got my brainiac friend Fereena to look into it for me, but all that nerd talk was a bit too much for me. She blew a gasket when I told her that, so... could you maybe ask her about it for me? In layman's terms, maybe?

We meet again! It's me, Walken the deacon. Recently, my attention was drawn toward a mysterious, glowing, rainbow coin that was found in the nearby Bapharian ruins. While I would love to get it myself, a certain someone has been quite firm in saying that if she has to send out another search party for me, it'll be coming out of my research funding. Surely, you understand. Could you go find it for me instead?

I'm Kurt! My dad sells fruits and veggies! My friend Reuben's a dairy farmer, and he's got this Bapharian thingy that I totally know would help with our sales and stuff! I really, really want it! But I dunno if it'd be convincing if a kid like me went and asked about it... So could you do it for me? It'll be for our store and stuff! Please?

Why, hello there. I'm a traveling puppeteer by the name of Paolo. I travel from town to town showing the children my puppet shows. I was putting on a performance in the plaza when my beloved Ellie went missing. She's a sweet little kitty puppet, my pride and joy, and my most precious friend. Please, please help me find her!

Hello! I am an actor by the name of Einhar. I've been doing some character studies for my next play, but I'm having a hard time really pinning mine down. I was hoping to find an acting partner to really help me nail the part when, lo and behold, the PERFECT person appeared! I have no idea who she is, but I NEED her. Could you please find her for me?!

My name is Telwa. I got a letter from my uncle, Blythe. Apparently, he ran into some trouble and needs someone to come see him. It's not exactly a place I can get to on my own, though. I know he's a really weird, stubborn old man, but could you please check up on him? Thank you very much.

I am a well-known financier in this town. My name is Manfred. My estate is currently under renovations. As such, I'd like to request that you retrieve a headboard I ordered from one of the greatest sculptors in Asterliese, Aurelee. It's long past the date he said it'd be completed, but I know the arts can be quite finicky! Really, I'm not the type to get angry over a little delay! Wahaha! If that headboard is complete, then please deliver it to me. If it's not, then asking him when he expects it to be complete will suffice.

Welcome, welcome! I'm Catrea, a businesswoman in search of a business partner! You ever heard of a thing called Khartoumian fangworks? It's a kind of craftmanship that was made back when the ancient desert city of Khartoum was in its heyday. It was unfortunately lost to the sands of time... but I want to bring it back! I just know it'd be GREAT for business! I can feel it in my bones! How about you? Think you can help me out?

My name is Rolle, a priestess with the Bapharian church. I received reports that dangerous monsters have appeared in <value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_055_area1]"/> within the Erstgreen Sands. What is most troubling is that I sent another adventurer to survey the area, but he has yet to return... Could you possibly find him and see if he is well?

Why, hello there, adventurer. Might I have a moment of your time? I'd like you to gather some hunting tools and deliver them to a young adventurer friend of mine. When I was younger, I used to gather them myself, but alas, these old bones fail me now. It's much more difficult for me than it used to be. I'm sure that it would be a simple task for a young adventurer like yourself though!

I am Berger, from the Development Bureau. I've only sent this quest out to adventurers I have high expectations for. Have you heard of a group of adventurers known as the Wyrm's Claws? They are the courageous souls who braved the Dragon's Rive for the very first time. The trail they walked is considered the first step into advanced adventuring. It's a harsh, unrelenting trail, but any who are able to traverse it will be henceforth known as an exceptional adventurer themself! Does that interest you? Then come on by!

I'm Kurt! I sell fruits and veggies! And I'm in big trouble! My little sister Tia's gone missing! She's blind, and I make it my duty to always stay by her side... but she's gone now! I don't know where she might've gone. I'm terrified someone kidnapped her... or maybe she's been attacked by some monsters... Please! I need you to help me find her!

Hey, I work in forestry here in Asteria. I need a favor from you. Lately, there's been a bunch of <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_005_enemy1]"/> making a mess of all the woods around here. It's gonna really mess with the value of the lumber here. Might even have to cut the damn things down and scrap 'em. Wild animals can have some impact on the industry and all, but we really can't let this keep up. Could you get out to <value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_005_area1]"/> and thin out the number of <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_005_enemy1]"/>?

Quest Information:
<value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_005_area1]"/>Defeat<value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_005_enemy1]"/>x [SQ102_005_num1]

Hey! We're a research team for Basdrolhin Memorial University! We're trying to look into something called muku markers. They're held by the <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_007_enemy1]"/> in the Halflight Hive. Muku markers look like just plain old rocks, but apparently the location and arrangement of rocks can warn the others of danger or tell them where they can find prey. If we can figure out what they mean, we might be able to avoid fighting muku altogether! Could you maybe make your way over to <value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_007_area1]"/> and collect some muku markers for us?

Quest Information:
<value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_007_area1]"/>: Gather muku marker x[SQ102_007_num1] from <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_007_enemy1]"/>

My name is Korra. I am the daughter of a wealthy and prominent merchant! Have you heard of azure glowblades? They are Bapharian relics that can be obtained from <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_008_enemy1]"/> that appear at the Pillar of Divinity. They glow a most brilliant blue, and are positively stunning to see! It's quite popular with children, so they are a must-have at parties. But alas, I've run out of stock and I've no clue what to do! You simply MUST go to<value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_008_area1]"/> and gather me some azure glowblades!

Quest Information:
<value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_008_area1]"/>: Gather azure glowblade x[SQ102_008_num1] from <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_008_enemy1]"/>

I am a history scholar by the name of Donny. I give regular lectures to students and would like to use some glass relics as visual aid. I'm just running low on them right now... The glassworks found around Bapharian ruins are completely different from the kind we use now. They're sturdy, intricate, and the shapes can be so complicated. Even present day artisans can see how valuable it is! I believe you should be able to find some at <value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_009_area1]"/>. Could you please get me some glass relics there?

Quest Information:
<value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_009_area1]"/>: Gather glass relic x[SQ102_009_num1] from mineral gathering

My name is Gaetan! Please, heed my call, Adventurer! I am in desperate need of the ironclad thread that <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_010_enemy1]"/> at the Pillar of Divinity drop! It's so thin, yet strong as an ox, if an ox were string! With that, I could fulfill my lifelong dream... That's right! I could make a yo-yo that wouldn't break no matter how violently a child throws it about! I WILL create this, or my name isn't Gaetan, the renowned children's toy maker! Adventurer! Take my hand! Now is your chance to revolutionize the toy world!

Quest Information:
<value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_010_area1]"/>: Gather ironclad thread x[SQ102_010_num1] from <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_010_enemy1]"/>

I'm Belinda... I'm a fortuneteller... I want some enlightenment crystals... You can find them in the desert. They're really beautiful and mysterious... They use it a lot in fortunetelling... The nicer crystal you have... The more convincing your fortunes should be... I bet people would even believe in MY fortunes... Even if I never get them right... Pretend you didn't hear that. Anyway, you can find enlightenment crystals on the <value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_012_area1]"/>... I'm counting on you...

Quest Information:
<value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_012_area1]"/>: Gather enlightenment crystal x[SQ102_012_num1] from mineral gathering

Okay, so here's the tea. Y'know how there are <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_013_enemy1]"/> on the Evenlee Terrace? Mmhmm, you heard me. <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_013_enemy1]"/>. It'd be major trouble if your average joe ran into one of 'em, y'know? Even a rookie adventurer would be "shook." So basically, I was thinkin' it'd be great if I could get some bigwig adventurer to come knock 'em around, right? It'd make everyone real happy and junk. And y'know, I'd totally be up for payin' good for it. Baron Radicool's always makes good on his word. Be sure you tell your friends how loaded and generous I am too!

Quest Information:
<value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_013_area1]"/>: Defeat<value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_013_enemy1]"/> x[SQ102_013_num1]

I'm Vespen, and I'm researching monster ecology. I'm currently studying how <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_014_enemy1]"/> burrow into the earth. I think there the key is probably hidden in their fangs somewhere, but I can't get hold of any good quality fangs. Could you possibly find me some sand viper twinfangs in the Erstgreen Sands? You should be able to find them by defeating the <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_014_enemy1]"/> that show up in <value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_014_area1]"/>. It'll help keep things safe in the desert too, so what've you got to lose?

Quest Information:
<value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_014_area1]"/>: Gather sand viper twinfang x[SQ102_014_num1] from <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_014_enemy1]"/>

I'm a doctor in Minsterhorn named Danae. I made a sleeping medicine because one adventurer asked me to, but now I've gotten a request to undo its effects by someone else. Apparently, the bastard was using my medicine to try and drug a girl. Can you believe these people? The damned creep was caught, thankfully, but his victim is still asleep. Could you try and get me the reviherbs I need to make her medicine? You can find them by checking the plants around <value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_021_area1]"/>.

Quest Information:
<value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_021_area1]"/>: Gather reviherb x[SQ102_021_num1] from plant gathering

The name's Hamilton. I'm a traveling salesman of precious metals and gems. Unfortunately, I'm running low on stock these days. I was supposed to have gotten some from Rietz, but there was a mix-up in addresses, and, well... Anyway, could you possibly pick up some galleil silver from <value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_023_area1]"/>? I'm on my way to the next town over, but I'll make arrangements with the Bureau to get it to me. Thanks a ton!

Quest Information:
<value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_023_area1]"/>: Gather galleil silver x[SQ102_023_num1] from mineral gathering

This is an official bounty quest from the Development Bureau. Please defeat the <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_201_enemy1]"/> and <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_201_enemy2]"/> that can be found on the <value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_201_area1]"/> in the Erstgreen Sands. Travel within the desert is exceptionally difficult. We must do whatever we can to prevent it from being more dangerous than it already is. It's our mission as adventurers and members of the Development Bureau to protect the peace! Please lend us your assistance!

Quest Information:<value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_201_area1]"/>: Defeat <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_201_enemy1]"/> x[SQ102_201_num1]
<value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_201_area2]"/>: Defeat 
<value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_201_enemy2]"/> x[SQ102_201_num2]

This is an official gathering quest from the Development Bureau. Please harvest and deliver drygrass fruit to the Bureau. It can be found in the <value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_206_area1]"/> in the Erstgreen Sands. There are many monsters who enjoy this fruit, so this will thin out their numbers and allow us to research the composition of the fruit itself. The Bureau and adventurers within are invaluable to artistic and societal progress! Come help society a better place!

Quest Information:
<value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_206_area1]"/>: Gather drygrass fruit x[SQ102_206_num1] from plant gathering

I'm Uro the woodworker. I've been collecting goblin accessories out of curiosity lately. I think demi-human artistic sensibilities are fascinating. I just know I can get a lot of inspiration from their designs. Problem is, all that artwork they've worked so hard on tends to get taken by force by stronger foes. That's where you come in. I want you to pick off a few <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_211_enemy1]"/> at the <value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_211_area1]"/> and pick up a few barbarian crests. I feel bad about sneaking in and stealing, but... y'know. Good luck!

Quest Information:
<value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_211_area1]"/>: Gather barbarian crest x[SQ102_211_num1] from <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_211_enemy1]"/>

This is the office of Basdrolhin University. Some of our students got a little... overzealous with an experiment with some... explosive results. Unfortunately, it's depleted our stock of teslam toxins as well. It's a crucial insulating component we use in great quantities for research into Bapharian relics, and as-such, our research has been brought to a stand-still. Could you defeat the <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_212_enemy1]"/> in the <value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_212_area1]"/> and collect some teslam toxins for us? And by some, I mean a LOT. It's in the grand pursuit of knowledge! Please help us!

Quest Information:
<value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_212_area1]"/>: Gather teslam toxin x[SQ102_212_num1] from <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_212_enemy1]"/>

Okay, so here's the tea. Okay, y'know how there are <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_213_enemy1]"/> in the Halflight Hive, right? Like, bigtime <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_213_enemy1]"/>s, y'know? They've got some SWEET succulent meat on 'em, y'know? You batter those bad boys and fry 'em up and you're in for a whole new world of flavor, y'know? I've got this party comin' up and I figure if I put up some snacks and stuff, it'll be totally lit for everyone. So like, that's why I'm asking for your help. Just call me Based Baron Radicool! Make sure you tell your friends I'm 'hella' generous too!

Quest Information:
<value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_213_area1]"/>: Gather succulent arachnocrab meat x[SQ102_213_num1] from <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_213_enemy1]"/>

It's me Aleni! I run the spiciest shop in Asterliese!
My regulars were telling me about some super spicy peppers called salamanero peppers. Apparently, they used to eat them in Salamzahd, but it's too much of a pain to get, so it's kinda fallen outta favor. I haven't really gotten anything new on my menu lately, so I'd LOVE to try and get some of those peppers to try myself! You're supposed to be able to find them on the <value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_214_area1]"/>, so could you go out there and find some for me?

Quest Information:
<value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_214_area1]"/>: Gather salamanero pepper x[SQ102_214_num1] from plant gathering

I'm Paolo. I travel from town to town putting on puppet shows for the people. I've been thinking of putting on a new show, but I haven't put the finishing touches on the leading songstress's costume just yet. I want to give her a tiara that demonstrates her nobility and elegance, and to do that, I'd like the petals of the gracetree flower. You should be able to find them on the <value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_215_area1]"/>. Can I ask you to find them for me? You'll be helping her reach stardom!

Quest Information:
<value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_215_area1]"/>: Gather gracetree flower petal x[SQ102_215_num1] from plant gathering

I am Gilesse, a butler. I look after a prominent figure's garden, and there is one feature I'd like to use above all else. Have you heard of a stone called a geminate skystone? They can be found in the <value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_216_area1]"/>. If you split them in two and separate them, it releases a small amount of flux. I would like to make a flower bed using these stones. Could I ask you to find them for me?

Quest Information:
<value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_216_area1]"/>: Gather geminate skystone x[SQ102_216_num1] from mineral gathering

I'm a restorer of Bapharian relics! Er, one in training, that is! And my name's Syree! I'm always happy to be of service! Er, but wait, I'm here to ask YOU for YOUR service, sorry! I need some windless tumbleweed. They look like little plants that tumble around even when there's not wind to blow 'em. I wanna see if we can use 'em to replace some the central workings of some of these relics. They sometimes get caught on the roots of other plants too. So yeah! Try and look around the plants on the <value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_217_area1]"/>!

Quest Information:
<value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_217_area1]"/>: Gather windless tumbleweed x[SQ102_217_num1] from plant gathering

This is a request from the Bapharian temple in Salamzahd. The quality of the water in the oasis here has worsened. The population of Salamzahd has grown considerably in recent years, but the quality of our waterways has, unfortunately, not been able to keep up. We'd like you to gather strainer stones that can be found on <value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_218_area1]"/>. Strainer stones are stones that have eroded to create many fine holes across them. These holes help filter out impurities in the water. We'd like to put them in the water in our oasis and see if it helps.

Quest Information:
<value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_218_area1]"/>: Gather strainer stone x[SQ102_218_num1] from mineral gathering

Hiii. Tynie the maid here. Ugh, I'm too tired for this... There are these monsters called <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_219_enemy1]"/> on <value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_219_area1]"/>. Ever heard of 'em? Well, they've been making a real mess of my master's chicken coops. I'm stuck having to chase down all the loose chickens now. Sucks, right? It'd be even more of a pain if they came back and broke it again, so could you go fight the <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_219_enemy1]"/> off for me? Uuugghhh, I seriously don't wanna hunt for some stupid chickens... Make sure you show those <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_219_enemy1]"/> what for so they don't come crawling back or whatever.

Quest Information:
<value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_219_area1]"/>: Defeat <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_219_enemy1]"/>

Isaac the miner here! Believe it or not, this is a true story, okay? I was walking around the <value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_220_area1]"/> when this real nasty wind came blowin', right? I was all freaked out about it when suddenly... there it was! A <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_220_enemy1]"/>! I just about jumped outta my skin, but I'm sure an adventurer could take the thing out, right? won't be able to sleep knowing that THING is out there, y'know? I'd seriously appreciate it!

Quest Information:
<value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_220_area1]"/>: Defeat <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_220_enemy1]"/>

We are the merchant guild Mirage from Salamzahd. We'd like you to come pick off the <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_221_enemy1]"/>that keep terrorizing our merchants on <value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_221_area1]"/>. These monsters have even bested Salamzahd's hunters too many times to count now. A few of the younger hunters have gotten it in their heads that they'd be the ones to slay the things, but they're just not strong enough. Could you go out there and get rid of them before those hotheads get themselves in a world of trouble?

Quest Information:
<value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_221_area1]"/>: Defeat <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_221_enemy1]"/>

I'm Tollegno, the painter. I painted a picture of a girl that sold for much higher than I thought it would, and I've gotten a new commission in. I'm worried about my paint supplies, though. I heard there are a lot of <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_222_enemy1]"/> showing up in the <value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_222_area1]"/> lately. There's a plant there that makes the perfect shade of blue, and I know they'll wind up mussing it all up. Could you please chase off those <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_222_enemy1]"/> for me before we lose that shade of blue?

Quest Information:
<value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_222_area1]"/>: Defeat <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_222_enemy1]"/> x[SQ102_222_num1]

I am Rosita of the Argerich family. I look after the sand silkworms who make our famous crystalsilk. Are you aware that the number of <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_223_enemy1]"/> in the <value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_223_area1]"/> has grown? Our sand silkworms mix the sands in the <value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_223_area1]"/>, but with <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_223_enemy1]"/> digging around there, it changes the mixture altogether. I'd like to ask you to take care of those <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_223_enemy1]"/> for us. This is such an important part of our desert culture. Could you be a dear and help us?

Quest Information:
<value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_223_area1]"/>: Defeat <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_223_enemy1]"/> x[SQ102_223_num1]

Howdy! The name's Mache. I'm a farmer here in Minsterhorn. My baby sheepies've gotten themselves in a real tizzy over the weird weather lately. Poor baby Caroline... Lucas... Sadir... Detonation Danny... What's that look for? Them's the name of my babies! Never you mind that though, I'm wantin' to find some sleepysheep herbs to mix in with their meals. It'll help calm their nerves, y'see! You can get them herbs out on the <value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_224_area1]"/>. But y'all be careful out there, 'cause monsters tend ta loiter around there!

Quest Information:
<value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_224_area1]"/>: Gather sleepysheep herb x[SQ102_224_num1] from plant gathering

Aker the miner here. My stock of prospectagua's run out. We use it to differentiate between ores around here. It's this special kinda water that's got flux runnin' through it and changes colors when it touches ore. You should be able to find it in the <value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_225_area1]"/>. Could you get some for us? It'll help us find new veins, and you bet we'll be digging up a storm once we do!

Quest Information:
<value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_225_area1]"/>: Gather prospectagua x[SQ102_225_num1] from water gathering

We're Limestone, a hotel chain doing business in the Rietz area. The other day, a fight broke out between some of our valued patrons. A part of the mosaic we have in the lobby was damaged in the chaos. It's quite an old piece of art, and it needs very special materials to restore it. Would you be able to procure the kaleidostones found on the <value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_226_area1]"/>? We would greatly appreciate it.

Quest Information:
<value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_226_area1]"/>: Gather kaleidostone x[SQ102_226_num1] from mineral gathering

This is a request from the Bapharian Templars in Salamzahd. We'd like to ask you to eliminate the <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_227_enemy1]"/> on the <value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_227_area1]"/>. The monsters in the Erstgreen Sands are particularly powerful. We've tried to take them out ourselves, but frankly speaking, there are more of them than there are of us. It is the church's duty to ensure the people's safety. Thus, we'd like to ask an adventurer to assist us in this endeavor. We would greatly appreciate it.

Quest Information:
<value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_227_area1]"/>: Defeat <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_227_enemy1]"/> x[SQ102_227_num1]

I am Manfred. I manage the farms here in Salamzahd. You've seen how the climate here in the Erstgreen Sands is, yes? It's difficult enough to grow my crops with how dry it is, but now we have some brigands rushing in and messing up my fields too! They call themselves <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_228_enemy1]"/>. Ordinary adventurers can't hold a candle to them! I don't care who does it! Somebody get rid of them for me! They're holed up in the <value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_228_area1]"/>. Now make them pay!

Quest Information:
<value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_228_area1]"/>: Defeat <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_228_enemy1]"/>

I'm Dean, the treasure hunter! The other day, I had a spectacular new encounter on the <value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_229_area1]"/>. I found what I believe to be yet unexplored ruins, and I tell you, my heart sang at the prospect! Unfortunately, that joy was soon shattered by unrelenting fear. For what should I find, but <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_229_enemy1]"/> prints! I'm just an explorer! I don't do fighting! But if I don't, I can't go into those ruins I longed to see! Please clear the way for me!

Quest Information: 
<value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_229_area1]"/>: Defeat <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_229_enemy1]"/>

I'm Lamare, wife of a merchant. A carriage carrying some of our products was attacked by a bunch of monsters in the <value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_230_area1]"/>. The coach managed to get by unscathed, but our merch is completely unusable now. This isn't the first time this has happened, either. I'm worried our customers are going to start losing faith in us, so I'd like to ask you to defeat the <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_230_enemy1]"/> for us. This'll also help keep the road safe as well, so please give it some thought.

Quest Information:
<value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_230_area1]"/>: Defeat <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_230_enemy1]"/> x[SQ102_230_num1]

Hey there. Hunter from Salamzahd here. Name's Jin. You know of the <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_231_enemy1]"/> that pop up in <value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_231_area1]"/>? They've got this super tough exoskeleton and fly around making our lives hell. Not to mention they've got a nasty temper and love terrorizing people. Us hunters have a long history with the things. Anyway, the <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_231_enemy1]"/> population has skyrocketed and frankly, we're fallin' to pieces. You think you could help us cut down a few?

Quest Information:
<value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_231_area1]"/>: Defeat <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_231_enemy1]"/> x[SQ102_231_num1]

Mercenary Suzette here. You know the Soundless City? It's some ancient city or sommat. It's got all sorts of relics that make me feel all mushy and corny. You could say I'm pretty fond of it. Unfortunately, a buncha monsters have been makin' themselves at home there. I'm not really suited for the whole 'standing guard' thing, but I can't just sit back and watch. Could you pick a <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_232_enemy1]"/> or two off for me in the Soundless City? It'd make my life a whole lot easier. Thanks!

Quest Information:
<value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_232_area1]"/>: Defeat <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_232_enemy1]"/> x[SQ102_232_num1]

I am butler by the name of William. The young master I serve has taken an interest in bug collecting as of late. As such, he's begun insisting I find him some bugs at the Halflight Hive. I've asked for several bodyguards to accompany me, but failure to prepare is preparing to fail. Would you be so kind as to go to the <value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_233_area1]"/> and defeat some <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_233_enemy1]"/> for us in advance? I believe once you have, I will be able to safely procure some insects out of their thinned numbers. I hope you'll assist in making my young master's dreams come true.

Quest Information:

The only problem is that there's a whole gang of brigands around there too! I'm pretty sure if we leave them be, they're gonna wreck the place. Unfortunately, fighting isn't exactly my forte. I'm more of a digging and excavating kinda person, y'know? Could you fight off the brigands on <value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_234_area1]"/> for me?

They should be at the Hunters' Camp in the Shimmering Valley and at Explorer's Haunt on Old Rainfall Road. Give 'em a shout if you see 'em! Gotta show extra care for every customer, y'know?

This is an official dungeon survey request from the Development Bureau. We are requesting adventurers survey the Thieves' Falls in the Minster Hills. Bands of thieves have made the caves their base of operations on occasion. We'd like to see what they've taken, what they've left behind, and why they choose that area to be their base. Please begin a survey of the Thieves' Falls at your nearest convenience. We appreciate your cooperation!

Quest Information:
Complete Thieves' Falls: Survey

This is an official dungeon survey request from the Development Bureau. We are requesting adventurers survey the Skyspire Ruins in the Andra Basin. Though it is known for its towering appearance, it's a Bapharian relic whose usage is still unclear to this day. There are countless theories for its' purpose... That it was to observe the heavens. That it was to convey messages to people in faraway lands. That it was a symbol of authority. That it was a cannon of sorts... but we still don't know for certain. Please begin a survey of the Skyspire Ruins at your nearest convenience. We appreciate your cooperation!

Quest Information:
Complete Skyspire Ruins: Survey

This is an official dungeon survey request from the Development Bureau. We are requesting adventurers survey Candlemere Tomb in the Shimmering Valley. It's said that any who try to take the treasures from within this shrine will be cursed with a terrible blight. We've even heard some adventurers met... untimely fates there as well. Oh, but we don't know if those rumors are true! Anyway, we can't let people worry needlessly, right? Please begin a survey of Candlemere Tomb at your nearest convenience. We appreciate your cooperation!

Quest Information:
Complete Candlemere Tomb: Survey

They might've missed a monster or two, or heaven forbid, some treasure! Good luck on the resurvey!

吟遊詩人のアドニスと言います。
画家だった父の遺品が輸送中に行方不明になりました。運んでいた荷馬車がモンスターに襲われてしまったそうです。
今ならまだ、アステリア平原の街道沿いに落ちているはずです。
僕が遺品を探す間の護衛をお願いします。

俺は農夫のマンダだ。野菜のためにすべてを懸けている！
実は、村に荒れ放題になっている畑があるんだ。他人の畑とはいえ、嘆き悲しむ野菜たちを見て見ぬふりはできない！
どうか俺と一緒に、あの荒れた畑を手入れしてほしい！

やっ、あたし、ミンスターホルンのエリカだよ。
実はさ……あたし、その……マンダのオッサンのこと、好きになっちゃったかも……。
お礼も兼ねてオッサンにプレゼント贈りたいんだ。相談に乗ってもらえないかな？

バファリア教の巡礼団に同行していましたレシと申します。
バハマール高原で亜人のモンスターたちが巡礼者を襲うという痛ましい事件が後を絶ちません。
彼らが安心して巡礼に向かえるよう、街道の<value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_039_enemy1]"/>を退治したいのです。
巡礼者のため、どうか力を貸していただけませんか？

冒険者のクリフです。極度の恥ずかしがり屋なので、メモを使わないと会話ができません。
実は届け物の依頼を受けたのですが、考えてみたら受取人と話せません！　顔を合わせるだなんて、とてもとても！
どうか僕の代わりに荷物を届けてもらえないでしょうか？

ラルパルに巡礼にまいりましたレナータと申します。
ここへ来る途中、大事な手紙を落としてしまいましたの。けれど、モンスターのいる場所ですから取りに戻ることもできませんで……。
もしよろしければ、お助けいただけないかしら？

こちらはメモリスタンドです。
お客様にさらなるサービスを提供するため、新商品を開発中です。
そこで必要な材料を発注したのですが、隊商が『<value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_239_area1]"/>』で足止めされてしまいました。
<value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_239_enemy1]"/>が運搬ルートの近くに出没しているそうです。
安全確保と新商品開発のために、『<value type="locationName" id="[SQ102_239_area1]"/>』の<value type="enemyName" id="[SQ102_239_enemy1]"/>を討伐してください。

お店の機械を適当にいじってたら、変な文字が浮かんできたの！
『塔の指定階層へ到達でエラー解除』だって。
あ、うん。機械は故障して動かなくなったよ？
ちんぷんかんぷんだけど、きっとアレだよ！　『始まりの塔』！
あそこを登ってみればいいんじゃないかな。
お姉さんにバレる前に、お願い！　行ってきて！

しかも、そのパーツは今、流通してないんだって！

The Case of the Night Carriage Attack
I Think This’ll Sell Like Hotcakes!
The Essence of the Pillar of Divinity
All Eyes On That Summer Prize!

Hello, my name is Surho. I work at The Rose Garden. A customer of ours gave us a plant I’ve never seen before. It’s supposed to have magnificent flowers, but no matter how long I wait, it never seems to bloom. I’ve tried a few different things , but I’m at a loss here... Can you help me find a way to get this strange rose to bloom?

My name is Monica. You won’t believe what I saw the other day. Surho, MY childhood friend, gave a bouquet of roses to an older woman! What’s going on between them? I need to know, but I’m too scared to ask him myself... Please find out who this other woman is! Thanks!

Hey it’s Isaac the miner. Well, I’m a miner in training under the big bossman Baumann, anyways. Just my luck, I went and lost something crazy important (and expensive) in a cave... I gotta report back to the big boss, but I’m so scared of what he’ll say that my legs are all wobbly. You gotta report back to him for me! Please!

The name’s Baumann, foreman of the mines. I know the veins in this area like the back of my hand, and have kept notes on ‘em since forever ago. All the sudden, some veins I’ve never seen before started showing up in my notes. I have a hard time believing there’s ore around here that I don’t know about, but I don’t have the manpower to check ‘em out. Can you go and see if these veins are for real?

That face. That physique. You’ve got that STAR quality, babe! I’m Bernadette, the world’s first adventurer agent. So, how ‘bout it?! Ready to take the adventuring world by STORM?! Stick with me and you’ll have it all: fame, fortune, and more luno than you know what to do with. Come on, it’s time to take your first step down the path to STARDOM!

Hello, my name is Lasha. I look after our miners here at the Rietz Mining Company We have one young buck by the name of Aker who has been dragging his feet lately. I know something must be going on between him and his girlfriend, but I can’t just go butting into my subordinate’s private life, can I? As much as I’d like all the juicy details, be a dear and get to the bottom of it for me so things don’t get complicated. Thanks.

Heya, Doc Volker here. There’s a sketchy drug making the rounds these days people are calling an “Aberration Blocker”. The Bapharian Church has asked me to give ‘em a hand with it, but I need to bring in some extra muscle. Can you help me get my hands on a sample of the stuff so I can see what it’s made of?

My name is Uro, and I’m a woodworker by trade. This area has some amazing wood for carving, but it isn’t something I can just chop down in the forest. It’s actually more of an ancient relic, making it hard for those of us who can’t fight to get our hands on. There isn’t much of it left, so I’d like you to get some for me before it’s gone forever.

It’s your boy Galvin, the traveling peddler. I’m trying to set up shop here in Salamzahd, but someone’s been giving me trouble. No, it’s not a rival business or anything like that. Travelers have been getting attacked on the road between Salamzahd and Rietz. If we don’t do something about it, my business won’t be the only one suffering, ya feel me? Can you get this sorted out? I’m trying to make some money over here!
Hi, I’m Paisley, a fellow adventurer. I came to...wherever I am right now on a request and kind of got lost. So yeah...can you please take me to somewhere called “Dragon’s Rive”? Thanks in advance!

The name’s Mino. Don’t forget it, because I’m the singular strongest hero who ever lived! You thought I was a soldier? Well, the old me is DEAD. The new me stands alone as the strongest hero now, and I’ll fight you to keep my place at the top of the mountain! ALONE, because that’s how I stand! We’ll decide here and now which one of us is the strongest! Bright it on!

Greetings fellow adventurer, my name is Aaron. I’m searching for a flower called the “Lumenflower” that blooms in this area. It’s an exceedingly rare desert flora only mentioned in legends. It’s the kind of thing that really piques our adventurer’s curiosity, isn’t it? Think you could lend me a hand in getting my hands on it?

I’m Quan, resident healer here in Salamzahd. Do you know of the adventurer named Zulka? I used to look after her in the past, but it seems she’s been feeling under the weather lately. Her tendency to not know when to rest has me a bit worried, so I’d like you to deliver some medicine to her.

Hi, my name is Bale. My family has lived here in Salamzahd for generations. I was cleaning out the attic of my shed and stumbled across what looks like a Bapharian relic. According to the note that was with it, my late father must have borrowed it from someone a long time ago. It’s probably been long forgotten, but I’d still like to get it back to its rightful owner. Can you help me track them down?

I’m Sabrina, a girl who loves song, theater, drama...all of the arts, really. The one who has stolen my heart and refuses to give it back is an exceptional talent among rising stars named Einhar. What I want from you is what any lover of the arts would want... GET ME HIS AUTOGRAPH! PLEASE! I need it. Thanks.

My daddy is a traveling painter, so he’s always leaving me at home ALL ALONE. This time, he went to Rietz and left a note saying he was gonna paint the mountains or something. I’m so BORED without him! Find my daddy and tell him to come back home!

Hello, I’m Emily, the aspiring actress! Unfortunately, my parents don’t approve of my dream at all. I’ve tried to convince them so many times, but it’s been like talking to a wall. All the sudden, my father said he would give me a challenge to complete. If I succeed, then he’ll have to give me his blessing, right? Can you help me make my dream come true?

I am Cyan of the Development Bureau. We have recently confirmed several cases of cemeteries across Asteria Plains being vandalized by someone or something. I dispatched my subordinate, Cecile, to investigate the matter. However, something is amiss. Cecile has a good head on her shoulders, but she seemed oddly distraught before departing. I would like you to lend her your assistance.

My name is Paula, a cafe waitress. One of our regular customers by the name of Catherine has forgotten her handkerchief. Normally, one of our staff would return it to her as soon as possible, but we’ve been so busy that no one has had the time. Sorry to bother, but can you please deliver the forgotten handkerchief to Ms. Catherine?

I am Bafit, the artisan calligrapher. Long have I attempted to promote the art of calligraphy. My request, however, concerns my granddaughter, Lindsey. Though she has agreed to becoming my successor, I fear that she is merely doing so out of concern for me. I would like to know how she truly feels, and have written her a letter. Please deliver it to Lindsey and listen to what she has to say.

Tragedy has befallen a merchant in our very own Asterliese! A dastardly crime has been committed under the cover of darkness. The Case of the Night Carriage Attack is afoot! I, Guido, detective extraordinaire, will crack this case wide open! With your assistance, of course. Come, there isn’t a moment to lose!

Greetings. I am Isabel, librarian under employ of the Development Bureau. I am in charge of the organization and lending of books in Lestor’s Bookshelves. There is a particular book that is overdue, and I would like to request your help in seeing it returned. Please contact the borrower, and let him know his book is past-due. Thank you.

Hello there, it’s Manfred, the landowner. Recently, a flock of Maskastrophe have been showing up in my fields. I’ve never seen anything quite like it. No matter how many times I drive them off, they just come right back. I’d like you to get to the bottom of this.

hey so today I was playing with my green pineapple friend like I always do but then a purple pineapple came and stole my toy so I tried to get it back but my mom said it was too dangerous please beat up that bad purple pineapple and get my toy back for me please thank you

My name is Clive, and I’m an adventurer. I have a son who thinks the world of me, so I went and told him that his old man could do anything. Of course, he believed me, and now I’ve bitten off more than I can chew. I don’t want to let him down, though... I’m begging you, help me to be as cool as my boy thinks I am!

Adventurers are no strangers to danger, and neither am I...but the danger I’m facing right now is going BROKE! So, I’m working on a new product to help right this sinking ship! Oh, trust me, it’s a GREAT idea! All we need now are to gather some materials! That’s where YOU come in! We need you to gather some things from <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ103_103_enemy1]"/> so we don’t have to get ourselves killed trying to!

My name is Andrew, I study the ecology of the flora and fauna of Asteria Plains for the Development Bureau. Recently, I ran across something that caught my attention. There have been reports of <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ103_104_enemy1]"/> sightings in Asteria Plains, which aren’t native to the area at all. They’re carnivorous and incredibly dangerous monsters. If there’s been some kind of change in <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ103_104_enemy1]"/> ecology, it could lead to serious problems. We need your help to identify the cause and exterminate these <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ103_104_enemy1]"/> before things get out of control.

My name is Sonia, and I enjoy collecting insects. No one really understands me, but I think insects are the most beautiful things in the world. The way their wings glisten and flutter, or the smooth sheen of their shells... It’s as though they were sent from heaven itself simply to make known and punish the ugliness of mankind. That being said, there are some insects I simply can’t even get near if I want to stay alive. Please go and gather some giant bugs for me!

You’re looking great out there, babe. KILLING IT! That star quality of yours is only growing. You haven’t forgotten about your agent, have you? It’s me, Bernadette! The worlds first (and best) adventurer agent! I’m going to pitch you again as the Bandit Butcher, and have a plan for it that the bureau will HAVE to bite on! So what’ll it be, babe? Ready to join forces again? This time, we won’t stop until you’re a household name!

Mino here. Still standing alone, but this time as the LONE STRONGEST BOUNTY HUNTER! Feel free to travel the world in search of a better (or stronger) bounty hunter than than me. I promise, they don’t exist. Because I ALONE am the best and strongest one there is! You want my title? THEN COME AND GET IT! Time to put this debate (that doesn’t exist because I’m the best) to rest! YOU. ME. LET’S GO!

Mino here! Get ready to feast your eyes on the most powerful solo (that means alone) ALL-ROUNDER! Soldier, Hero, Bounty Hunter... I’ve gone by many titles in my time, but I plan to surpass all of them as an all-rounder! ALONE! You think you have what it takes to best the best? There’s only room for one most powerful solo all-rounder to stand alone! It’s time to settle this once and for all! I CHALLENGE YOU! LET’S GOOO!

Hello, my name is Nene. My friend Toto is really bad at rock paper scissors. It’s so easy to tell what he’s going to throw next. I keep trying to help, but he just gets mad at me. I was hoping an adventurer could help me get through to him.

Good day, my friend. You must be a skilled adventurer. Stay a while and listen to this old man’s story, would you? I’m in need of precious materials only found in <value type="locationName" id="[SQ103_110_area1]"/> to restore an ancient work of art called “Rattranier's Stairway”. It’s an exceedingly dangerous place, so even the most seasoned of adventurers may find this request difficult to complete. There’s no need to accept if you are not up to the task, but if you are, then feel free to contact me for more details.

I am Belinda, the fortune teller... I know many do not believe in my profession...but there is something I would like your assistance with regardless... My visions have shown me several individuals with poor fortunes... We must prevent them from happening...

I am Belinda, the fortune teller... I recently told the fortune of a young woman...but what I told her did not match what I witnessed in my visions... Nothing bad will happen...but I fear she may be disappointed because of my deception... I know this is wrong of me to ask...but can you please ensure her fortune comes to pass?

Hello there. I’m Cecile from the Development Bureau. <value type="locationName" id="[SQ103_003_area1]"/> is a veritable treasure trove of medicinal herbs to those in the know. Many of the materials used to craft precious recovery items used by adventurers are often gathered there. However, the dramatic increase in the <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ103_003_enemy1]"/> population has taken its toll on the vegetation of <value type="locationName" id="[SQ103_003_area1]"/>. If this continues, there won’t be enough medicinal herbs to go around. Please help us protect these herbs by defeating <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ103_003_enemy1]"/>!

Quest Information:

My name is Manfred and I run a farm in Salamzahd. The sandstorms in the area have been blocking out the sun. A break from the heat is nice, but it’s a problem when my crops don’t get enough sunlight and yields go down. There’s not much we can do about it when it’s just the weather, but the cause is those <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ103_004_enemy1]"/> that have been crawling around <value type="locationName" id="[SQ103_004_area1]"/>. If you can get rid of the <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ103_004_enemy1]"/>, then there won’t be as much sand being kicked around and the problem should sort itself out. Thanks!

Quest Information:
[<value type="locationName" id="[SQ103_004_area1]"/>]: Defeat <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ103_004_enemy1]"/> x[SQ103_004_num1]

The name’s Blythe, and I dig holes in the desert. Been seeing some huge bird’s shadow on the ground in <value type="locationName" id="[SQ103_005_area1]"/>. Even I know it’s gotta be a Maskastrophe. I’m not to keen on becoming lunch for one of those things, so would you mind taking care of it? The less of those <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ103_005_enemy1]"/> around, the safer things will be for travelers and traders alike.

Quest Information:
[<value type="locationName" id="[SQ103_005_area1]"/>]: Defeat <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ103_005_enemy1]"/>

Hi, I’m Erika. I till the fields here in Minsterhorn. Lately, me and a bunch of the old guys around town have had an issue with our fields getting torn up. I know it’s those darn <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ103_006_enemy1]"/> in <value type="locationName" id="[SQ103_006_area1]"/>! Can you do something about it for us? Maybe if you take down a few of them, they’ll leave us alone. It sure would mean a lot to everyone in the village. You don’t even gotta say I asked you to do it. Just get those pesky <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ103_006_enemy1]"/> to knock it off!

Quest Information:
[<value type="locationName" id="[SQ103_006_area1]"/>]: Defeat <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ103_006_enemy1]"/> x[SQ103_006_num1]

Attention all anonymous collaborators. It has been confirmed that the <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ103_007_enemy1]"/> has malfunctioned. It must be stopped at once. Those who understand the threat should take immediate action. We await your report.

Quest Information:
[<value type="locationName" id="[SQ103_007_area1]"/>]: Defeat <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ103_007_enemy1]"/>

Good day to you. My name is Catherine. Have you heard rumors of the beauty potion making the rounds among the women of Asterliese? Apparently, it is an extract of shadow viper liver from the <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ103_009_enemy1]"/> in <value type="locationName" id="[SQ103_009_area1]"/>. It is said that drinking a decoction of it gives your skin a beautiful, youthful luster. I would very much like to stock this shadow viper liver to meet the high demand that is sure to follow. Could you procure a number of them as soon as possible?

Quest Information:
[<value type="locationName" id="[SQ103_009_area1]"/>]: Gather Shadow Viper Liver x[SQ103_009_num1] from <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ103_009_enemy1]"/>s

Hey there, it’s Mira the courier. My sweet Echo Mount can make it through just about anything this world throws at her, but the desert just rubs her the wrong way, if you catch my drift. She just hates getting covered in all that sand. I heard that if you use something called “Windbreak Oil” from a plant in <value type="locationName" id="[SQ103_010_area1]"/>, the sand just comes right off. Can you collect some for me? I’m willing to try anything, at this point.

Quest Information:
[<value type="locationName" id="[SQ103_010_area1]"/>]: Gather windbreak oil x[SQ103_010_num1] (plant)

I’m Lemare, the wife of a prestigious merchant. My husband is considering opening a restaurant, and is researching dishes for the menu. We are incredibly particular about the water our chefs use for cooking, and want to ensure it is of the finest quality. To that end, we would ask that you gather mountain spring water from <value type="locationName" id="[SQ103_021_area1]"/>. Thank you kindly for your assistance.

Quest Information:
[<value type="locationName" id="[SQ103_021_area1]"/>]: Gather Mountain Spring Water x[SQ103_021_num1]

I’m Lindsey the scribe. A customer of mine wants to express her passion not only through their words, but in the ink they’re written in as well! I thought changing the color of the ink might be a good way to do that. Would you be able to get me some scarlet ore from <value type="locationName" id="[SQ103_022_area1]"/>? I think with that, we should be able to make a red ink that won’t fade over time, and really help put some passion into her letters!

Quest Information:
[<value type="locationName" id="[SQ103_022_area1]"/>]: Gather Scarlet Ore x[SQ103_022_num1](mineral)

My name is Catrea, a merchant who deals in various lucrative ventures. I’ll be making several trips between Asterliese and Lallipar for business meetings concerning gemstones, but I hear that brigands often prey on merchants traveling those roads. Can you do me a favor and thin their ranks by defeating several<value type="enemyName" id="[SQ103_023_enemy1]"/>s in <value type="locationName" id="[SQ103_023_area1]"/>? Collect their telescopes while you’re at it. They use them to scope out potential marks, so the fewer they have to go around, the better. Help me get my business done, and I’ll make sure you’re compensated for it.

Quest Information:
[<value type="locationName" id="[SQ103_023_area1]"/>]: Gather Bandit Telescope x[SQ103_023_num1] from Bandit Scouts

So um...I’m a friend of Calvain’s... Someone from the Bapharian Church... I want you to go to a place called the Chained One's Spawnery, and um...defeat the monsters there. I don’t know all the details...but I was told to make this request. God requests the strength of those who understand what’s at stake. Blessed be the Bapharian God.

Quest Information:
[<value type="locationName" id="[SQ103_201_area1]"/>]: Defeat <value type="enemyName" id="[SQ103_201_enemy1]"/> x[SQ103_201_num1]
